bLA7o", "publicIdentifier": "johannes-steyn-b0602a2", "recommendations/0/context": "Johannes worked with Bijo on the same team", "recommendations/0/date": "September 16, 2021", "recommendations/0/description": "I worked with Bijo on two hotel openings that was both very challenging in their own way. He managed to make things happen regardless of the circumstances or challenges he was presented with.\n\nBijo was a very well respected member of the team and was always helpful to his subordinates and peers. Respectful of the different cultures and fitted in seamlessly, He also developed his team and other colleagues  and many of his subordinates were promoted due to his efforts . Bijo also put in a lot of effort to hone his own skills and further develop himself as well.\n\nI wish Bijo well with his future endeviours and would gladly work with him again. ", "recommendations/0/name": "Bijo Thomas,CPPM,CISCM", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Procurement Manager at Shangri-La The Shard, London", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/bijo-thomas-cppm-ciscm-9b17209/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAG1S5UBH387g39VcWLVocECn6yFpLLbSN8", "recommendations/1/context": "Johannes worked with Mohammed on the same team", "recommendations/1/date": "November 20, 2019", "recommendations/1/description": "I have worked with Mohammed for a period of almost 2 years. During this time he demonstrated being a highly skilled F&B operator setting up new outlets for Fauchon  and a new high end Ballroom.\n\nMohammed was leading the market in running high end outlets with and equally high end outside catering operation. From recruiting, to systems, to reports, budgets and P&L all were created by him and tailor made to suit his operational needs.\n\nMohammed is a very effective leader and runs his operations efficiently and smoothly with a keen eye for detail and profitability for the owners. His knowledge and experience in hospitality is at a very high level and he would prove himself to be an asset to wherever he decides to continue his career .", "recommendations/1/name": "Mohammed Bseiso", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "Founder & CEO at Kloud Virtual Concepts | Operator of Jordan’s Largest Self-Run Multi-Brand Virtual Food Court | Senior Hospitality Executive | F&B Strategy & Operations Consultant", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/mohammed-bseiso/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAMwfwoBBTBljgxB_a89sCaGO7phaHcukWo", "recommendations/2/context": "Johannes managed Patrick directly", "recommendations/2/date": "June 20, 2015", "recommendations/2/description": "Patrick is a very talented Pastry Chef.He manages a huge operation and always seems to have that extra bit of creativity. He is highly respected by his team and colleagues in the hotel and a true pleasure to work with.", "recommendations/2/name": "Patrick Vauthier", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Executive Pastry Chef & Culinary Project Manager Executives Chef", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/patrickvauthier/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAN4vg8Bn0Zy7OyfmytlYzuHstZB3ae16EA", "recommendations/3/context": "Johannes worked with Ali but on different teams", "recommendations/3/date": "October 12, 2013", "recommendations/3/description": "Ali was working with me in Kuwait. At that time I was the Culinary Director and we worked closely together on HR issues. Ali is a very organized individual and have a real passion for his colleagues. \n \nI would not hesitate to recomend him to any prospective employer. A nice guy to work with.", "recommendations/3/name": "Ali Naseredin ,SPHRi", "recommendations/3/subtitle": "General Manager at Continuous Development company", "recommendations/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ali-naseredin-sphri-04927449/", "recommendations/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAou-jkBZ4d7sD6BSOC869tkhADIpTCVS-Q", "recommendations/4/context": "Johannes worked with Martin but they were at different companies", "recommendations/4/date": "January 13, 2013", "recommendations/4/description": "I worked with Martin when I was the Area Executive Chef at Citystars Cairo. \n\nMartin is a Chef at heart  He has very good communication skills and has a thorough knowledge of what it takes to operate in the Hospitality Industry in a  constantly evolving environment. He can work independently and is able to effectively multi-task to ensure that tasks and projects are completed on time.  \n\nIt was a real pleasure dealing with him.", "recommendations/4/name": "Martin Kobald - ChefMLK", "recommendations/4/subtitle": "Principal Owner at ChefMLK Group of Companies", "recommendations/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/martin-kobald-chefmlk-a744ab16/", "recommendations/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAANGyjgBpiSZcB3foSkIGEZy2MYiNaRL93U", "recommendations/5/context": "Johannes was senior to Mona but didn't manage Mona directly", "recommendations/5/date": "February 16, 2012", "recommendations/5/description": "To whom it may concern,\n\nMona Jordanov worked with me at the Opening of Holiday Inn Sofia  as C&B Sales Coordinator.\n\nMona is a very conscientious person, can work independently and is able to effectively multi-task to ensure that tasks and projects are completed on time.  Mona has a very good understanding of the overall operational side of the business and is very adaptable when faced with difficult situations.   \n\nMona had an excellent rapport with her colleagues and guests. I would not hesitate to recommend her to any future employer.\n\nJohannes Steyn", "recommendations/5/name": "Mona Jordanov", "recommendations/5/subtitle": "Assistant Account Manager", "recommendations/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/mona-jordanov-85143a40/", "recommendations/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAibaz0BNnUf6-uAczGA_8rhyeq4WUT8534", "recommendations/6/context": "Johannes worked with Elitza but on different teams", "recommendations/6/date": "February 16, 2012", "recommendations/6/description": "To whom it may concern,\n\n\nElitza Velichkova worked with me at the Pre opening and Opening of Holiday Inn Sofia  as FOH Manager.\n\nElitza is a very conscientious person, can work independently and is able to effectively multi-task to ensure that tasks and projects are completed on time.  Elitza has a very good understanding of the overall operational side of the business and is very adaptable when faced with difficult situations. She was instrumental in opening of the Hotel and the setup of all the front off house systems.  \n\nElitza had an excellent rapport with her colleagues and guests. I would not hesitate to recommend her to any future employer.\n\nI want to wish her the best of luck with any future endeavors she chooses to pursue. \n\nJohannes Steyn", "recommendations/6/name": "Elitza Velichkova", "recommendations/6/subtitle": "General Manager at WorkFactory", "recommendations/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/elitza-velichkova-0a04bb35/", "recommendations/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAdfBbgBQxX_jMzH0nz_g810wJNxmE4QRSU", "recommendations/7/context": "Johannes managed Pierre directly", "recommendations/7/date": "February 16, 2012", "recommendations/7/description": "To whom it may concern,\n\n\nPierre Meintjes worked for me at Sage Restaurant as Partner, Executive Sous Chef and FOH Manager.\n\nPierre is a very conscientious person, can work independently and is able to effectively multi-task to ensure that tasks and projects are completed on time.  Pierre has a very good understanding of the overall operational side of the business and is very adaptable when faced with difficult situations. He was instrumental in the day-to-day running of our restaurant.  \n\nPierre had an excellent rapport with his colleagues and the guests. I would not hesitate to re-employ Pierre at any time and would also recommend him to any future employer.\n\nI want to wish him the best of luck with any future endeavors he chooses to pursue. \n\nPlease let me know if you have any further questions.\n\nRegards\nJohannes Steyn", "recommendations/7/name": "Pierre Meintjes", "recommendations/7/subtitle": "General Manager", "recommendations/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/pierre-meintjes-914a341b/", "recommendations/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAQ--yABAKdqYjzv2_xZofWty2CGfJq2RcE", "recommendations/8/context": "Johannes was senior to Ahmed but didn't manage Ahmed directly", "recommendations/8/date": "April 15, 2011", "recommendations/8/description": "Ahmed was working with me in Cairo at the Holiday Inn Citystars. At the time I was the Area Executive Chef and we worked closely together. Ahmed is a very organized individual and very goal orientated, He is fast, precise and also pasionate about his job. Ahmed was very well respected amongst the team and did not mind spending extra hours when needed in order to do his job. I would not hesitate to recomend him to any prospective employer.April 15, 2011", "recommendations/8/name": "Ahmed Said", "recommendations/8/subtitle": "General Manager", "recommendations/8/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ahmed-said-8161a220/", "recommendations/8/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAARMiBIB3OGyLJ_0gTfYrNx4nQkmEFHQo4A", "recommendations/9/context": "Johannes worked with Tatyana on the same team", "recommendations/9/date": "January 25, 2011", "recommendations/9/description": "Tatiana was working with me in Sofia for the Opening of the first Holiday Inn in Bulgaria. At that time I was the Executive Chef and we worked closely together. Tatiana is a very organized individual and together with her goal orientated thinking, it was a very smooth opening. She was fast, precise and also pasionate about her job.\n\nTatiana was very well respected amongst the team and did not mind spending extra hours when needed in order to achieve the targets and goals which were set. I would not hesitate to recomend her to any prospective employer.", "recommendations/9/name": "Tatyana Trufeva", "recommendations/9/subtitle": "Global Sales Specialist", "recommendations/9/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/tatianatrufeva/", "recommendations/9/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAJxWIgBAtgQKbXkw2cqekelWu2xcT54Nic", "recommendations/10/context": "Johannes worked with Chef. Gianfranco but they were at different companies", "recommendations/10/date": "September 18, 2010", "recommendations/10/description": "To whom it may concern,\n\nChef Gianfranco did a promotion for us in our Italian fine dining restaurant Maestro at the Intercontinental Cairo Citystars Egypt. \n\nDuring this period, Chef Gianfranco demonstrated a high degree of professionalism and dedication to his work. His communication skills allowed him to develop a productive working relationship with the local chefs, and he created a rich innovative menu.  He combined Italian cuisine with a slight Middle Eastern touch. His passion for food helped us run a very successful food promotion during the time he visited the Citystars complex.\n\nI can recommend Chef Gianfranco to any future employer.", "recommendations/10/name": "Chef. Gianfranco Chiarini.", "recommendations/10/subtitle": "🟢 Chef/Patron at Dieci Boutique Restaurant | 🏆 La Liste 2026 – Top 1000 | 🏆 Bacchus 2026 – Bulgaria’s Best 2025 | ♻️ SRA 2026 – 3 Stars ⭒⭒⭒ | ♻️ Green Key 2026 – Eastern Europe Most Sustainable.", "recommendations/10/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/chefchiarini/", "recommendations/10/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAKWouQBbzCVlrdgVcHDaG6aaD8gV09Q_is", "recommendations/11/context": "Johannes worked with Michael on the same team", "recommendations/11/date": "August 25, 2009", "recommendations/11/description": "Michael is a dedicated individual who focuses on delivering results. He is a hands-on manager who works closely with his team to increase overall F&B revenue and guest satisfaction. I highly recommend Michael to any future employer.  \n\nJohannes Mackenzie Steyn\nArea Executive Chef IHG Citystars", "recommendations/11/name": "Michael Farquhar", "recommendations/11/subtitle": "COO @ ETM Group | Hospitality Expert Guiding Profitable Concepts", "recommendations/11/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/farquhar/", "recommendations/11/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAHGmKcB1efHcn8lepDy9Yo-Zg94bHDsswg", "recommendations/12/context": "Johannes reported directly to Darren", "recommendations/12/date": "August 25, 2009", "recommendations/12/description": "This letter is a personal recommendation for Darren Darwin.  I have worked with Darren for several years.  He is a person with integrity, very dedicated, hard working and professional.  He is loyal to his staff, owners or any other people he deals with.  Darren has always been good motivating employees to strive for great guest satisfaction results.  He is also a hands-on manager who works closely with sales and marketing developing plans to increase revenue.\n\nI highly recommend Darren to any future employer.  He would be a great asset to any company.\n\nPlease feel free to contact me if you require any additional information.  My email address:  johannes.steyn@ihg.com\n\nJohannes Mackenzie Steyn\nArea Executive Chef IHG Citystars, Cairo, Egypt.", "recommendations/12/name": "Darren Darwin MBA", "recommendations/12/subtitle": "Dynamic GM/MD in Luxury Hospitality | Industry Acclaimed | Creative Storyteller | Human Capital and People Development Specialist | Growth Mindset | Transformation and Change Catalyst", "recommendations/12/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/darrendarwin/", "recommendations/12/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAMVhaAB4QNYGoQgY6HZ88MiruV1-tQ40_g", "skills/0/title": "Menu Development", "skills/1/title": "Hospitality Management", "skills/2/title": "Banquets", "skills/3/title": "Food & Beverage", "skills/4/title": "Hotels", "skills/5/title": "Cuisine", "skills/6/title": "Food Safety", "skills/7/title": "Staff Development", "skills/8/title": "Pre-opening", "skills/9/title": "Hotel Management", "skills/10/title": "Hospitality Industry