E_3EL-XxAX_3BHFQh7ubnR7w", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/public_identifier": "manoj-bastola-794040170", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAACiViGAB3ZWN5CInpFl5_0ops8kQGuuZTC8", "profilePic": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4D03AQGc2Ml7BF6ORg/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1722660729367?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=HLetYyuZDNPT_OZ7mUAg9lQKPxldnaTocQI7FhazWZU", "profilePicHighQuality": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4D03AQGc2Ml7BF6ORg/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1722660729367?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=HLetYyuZDNPT_OZ7mUAg9lQKPxldnaTocQI7FhazWZU", "publicIdentifier": "davidohanlon", "recommendations/0/context": "David Richard worked with Pathma but they were at different companies", "recommendations/0/date": "May 17, 2025", "recommendations/0/description": "I have dealt with Pathma for many years and found him to be extremely dedicated Executive Chef with a vast experience across numerous continents and multiple countries.\n\nHis immense experience & knowledge highlights why he is highly regarded across the culinary world in top end resorts and hotels. Smart, polite, open, honest and very well presented. He is the perfect example of an Ex. Chef who goes that extra mile ensuring a win win for his guests, team and owners alike. \n\nI can highly recommend Pathma at all levels.", "recommendations/0/name": "Pathma Bala", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Create your IDENTITY / Be a Leader / You're a Brand", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/pathmabala-executivechef/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAHAiK4BSx1zUd5qROXtYZxOD_7QjEVF6zA", "recommendations/1/context": "David Richard managed Ambarsari directly", "recommendations/1/date": "May 17, 2025", "recommendations/1/description": "Ambar worked for me at the Hotel Borobudur, Jakarta where she held the position of Dir' of Rooms. \n\nThis position in such an iconic and legendary property came with a lot of challenges, surprises and of course enjoyment. A 700 room property with 1400 personnel was never dull. Ambar handled all with aplomb and poise. Excellent at proactiveness and thinking out of the box.  \n\nExceptionally detailed, very strong work ethic, will work all hours, never leaves something undone, team player, smart, excellent customer contact, highly professional. \n \nI have no hesitation in recommending Ambar for any role in the industry and can see her in a GM role in the not too distant future.", "recommendations/1/name": "Ambarsari Rositaningrum", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "Director of Rooms", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ambarsari-rositaningrum-03a983113/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABxxOG4BF_I5rrsw1utvqja9kPLmG2DO4sY", "recommendations/2/context": "David Richard managed Syahban directly", "recommendations/2/date": "April 3, 2025", "recommendations/2/description": "I employed Syabhan at the Hotel Borobudur Jakarta as Dir' of Engineering.\n\nI can safely say that he re-organized the department in a very short space of time to what is expected of a 5* international hotel and its expectations. Without doubt a fantastic and knowledgeable engineer who is not afraid to speak his mind.\n\nTalented, driven, meticulous, great eye for detail and excellent at follow up. \nNo stone left unturned to find a solution for any challenge. \n\nI have no hesitation in recommending Syabhan to any future employer.", "recommendations/2/name": "Syahban Hasibuan", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Director Of Engineering Hotel Borobudur Jakarta", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/syahban-hasibuan-4a078438/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAfx-bgBZucGaoIoiomPx8kDjdC96QZ_qns", "recommendations/3/context": "David Richard was senior to Sania but didn't manage Sania directly", "recommendations/3/date": "April 3, 2025", "recommendations/3/description": "Sania is one of the most talented and customer focused front office managers in Pakistan. \n\nCalm, controlled, willing and able to find a solution to all the challenges that the industry throws at us. Her enthusiasm for the job is second to none and always with a smile.\n\nHer deep knowledge and understanding of operations in a very challenging environment enables her to bring a calm demeanor and professional approach to all situations. These skills allow her to approach her job with authority, talent and is and excellent mentor for those around her. \n\nHer approach to all who worked with her wants Sania to reach the top of our profession.\n\nI whole heartedly recommend Sania and wish her continued success in her career.", "recommendations/3/name": "Sania Akhtar", "recommendations/3/subtitle": "Assistant Front Office Manager", "recommendations/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sania-akhtar/", "recommendations/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAADn6IlQBm-tIDWDZQbRvK0bMJKF-uDcF2KY", "recommendations/4/context": "David Richard managed Indah Soesanti directly", "recommendations/4/date": "March 7, 2025", "recommendations/4/description": "Indah has been an inspiration and constant source of support. \n\nA great listener and understands both sides before she makes a decision to undertake. \nExtremely organized and talented at getting the best out of people. \nIndah has not only been a good friend & colleague but a voice of reason in a challenging environment.\n\nShe keeps her cool and does not show emotion under pressure. \nTo describe her, I can say skillful, adept, accomplished, masterful and polished - utterly professional.\n\nI have no hesitation in recommending her to any prospective employer or client.", "recommendations/4/name": "Indah Soesanti Bastian, S. Tr. Par., M. Par.", "recommendations/4/subtitle": "HR & GA Leader, Lecturer in Hospitality", "recommendations/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/indah-soesanti-bastian-s-tr-par-m-par-36359326/", "recommendations/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAVsyzsBVHuM927DPtIa3HzKYo4PICXQ3Og", "recommendations/5/context": "David Richard managed Gunung directly", "recommendations/5/date": "January 28, 2025", "recommendations/5/description": "Deca is currently my Revenue Guru at The Borobudur, Jakarta.\n\nWithout doubt one of the most talented and revenue focused hoteliers in Jakarta. Always willing and able to find a solution to all the challenges that the industry throws at us. His enthusiasm for the job is second to none. He has a deep knowledge and understanding of revenue management, thus enabling him to bring this skill to new practitioners of the art. \n\nHis approach to all who worked with him wants Deca to reach the pinnacle of our profession. In a nutshell an excellent professional and a pleasure to work with.", "recommendations/5/name": "Gunung Deca Riviera", "recommendations/5/subtitle": "Revenue and Ecommerce Manager at Borobudur Hotel, Jakarta", "recommendations/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/gunung-deca-riviera-138713b3/", "recommendations/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABgh6fwB7n1kAxfU-V10fo4WQS3mtgJ7vgY", "recommendations/6/context": "David Richard managed Ignatius directly", "recommendations/6/date": "January 28, 2025", "recommendations/6/description": "I have the pleasure of working with Danny as my DFB @ Hotel Borobudur, Jakarta.\n\nIn an extremely fast paced environment, Danny is a calm and cool head on a seasoned hospitality shoulders.  Due to his professionalism, work ethic, diligence and integrity I rely on him to run this huge operation, keep the associates on their toes and ensure a top class service to our discerning clientele. \n\nDanny is enthusiastic, understanding and extremely well liked by all his colleagues.\n\n I wish him continued success with HBJ all the best for his continued career.", "recommendations/6/name": "Ignatius Anugraham", "recommendations/6/subtitle": "Hotelier / Hospitality Industry", "recommendations/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ignatius-anugraham-3ab83131/", "recommendations/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAa1K_MB-glv_y9uOJOn9woDnw6vvXAVMb8", "recommendations/7/context": "David Richard managed Syed Mughees directly", "recommendations/7/date": "September 14, 2024", "recommendations/7/description": "Mughees is a professional Director of Human Resources that brought his considerable experience to the Marriott Islamabad. \n\nExcellent listener and understands both sides before he jumps. \nHis knowledge of local labour laws and government rules & regulations was a godsend when dealing with situations where needed.\n\nExtremely organized and talented at getting the best out of people. \n\nHe keeps his cool and does not show emotion under pressure. To describe him, he is - Professional, Fair, Open, Honest with the highest of Integrity.\n\nI have no hesitation in recommending him and would very happily work with him again.", "recommendations/7/name": "Syed Mughees Shah (SHRM-CP)", "recommendations/7/subtitle": "Director Human Resources | Strategic HR Leader | SHRM-CP | Driving Talent Transformation & Inclusion in Hospitality | Expert in Employee Engagement | Culture & Operational Excellence", "recommendations/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/mugheesshah/", "recommendations/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAImSRIBQ_mZ5yRfdH0sk9jRvC9j7VkeMuw", "recommendations/8/context": "David Richard managed Aamir directly", "recommendations/8/date": "June 8, 2024", "recommendations/8/description": "Aamir is a true hospitality professional.\n\nMotivated, driven, inspired and will always find a solution to all challenges.\nAn inspirational individual to work with. A work alcoholic who can see trends in the market place before anyone else. His contribution to the operational and fiscal success of the hotel was clear to all who worked with him. \n\nHighly groomed, articulate, very well presented and an all round hotel professional. \nAamir is every owner's dream as a GM who will be continually coming up with new ideas/promotions/campaigns to market and sell the property. \n\nI have no hesitation in recommending Aamir and would gladly and hopefully work with him again", "recommendations/8/name": "Aamir Khawaja", "recommendations/8/subtitle": "General Manager | Four Points by Sheraton Lahore (Marriott International) | Hospitality Leader Transforming Hotel Performance, Revenue Strategy & Guest Experience | Former Senior GM @ Centaurus Towers Residencia & Suites", "recommendations/8/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/aamirkhj/", "recommendations/8/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAN0fpwBmZWjm4ko-Cyqzqz-rdj6gSZmuDQ", "recommendations/9/context": "David Richard managed Asim directly", "recommendations/9/date": "May 17, 2024", "recommendations/9/description": "I had the pleasure of working with Asim @ Avari.\n\nAsim is an all round professional with extensive experience across all spheres in food and beverage. With his overseas exposure and knowledge he brings and international viewpoint to the table. \nDue to his work ethic, diligence, integrity and professionalism i recommended him to the Marriott in Karachi.\n\nI have no hesitation in recommending Asim and wish him all the best for his continued career.", "recommendations/9/name": "Asim Khalid", "recommendations/9/subtitle": "Corporate Head Food & Beverage/Acting Hotel Manager", "recommendations/9/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/asim-khalid-b3a6036/", "recommendations/9/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAEoQp4BXuERdJb2zQIWRVryovtjjTadSBg", "recommendations/10/context": "David Richard managed Nisha directly", "recommendations/10/date": "May 15, 2024", "recommendations/10/description": "I had the pleasure of working with Nisha @ Marriott where she was the Marketing & PR Manager. \n\nNisha was a gem to work with. Very well connected and knew the city, its happenings, the events where to maximize our exposure and gain the trust of the clientele with real time marketing.\nExcellent work ethic, diligence, integrity and utter professionalism. \n\nNisha has moved onto new and exciting challenges in the Gulf.  I have no hesitation in recommending Nisha and wish her all the best for her continued career.", "recommendations/10/name": "Nisha K.", "recommendations/10/subtitle": "Marketing Manager | Performance Marketing & Digital Growth | Hospitality", "recommendations/10/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/nisha-akhan/", "recommendations/10/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABk_Zb0BUZ6AB9q91mkIEsgEaYHutgM6Q84", "recommendations/11/context": "David Richard was senior to Alvin but didn't manage Alvin directly", "recommendations/11/date": "May 10, 2024", "recommendations/11/description": "I had the pleasure of working with Alvin at the Royal Cliff Hotels Group. \n\nWhen I joined in March 2007 he was the International Senior Sales Manager. Due to his work ethic, diligence, integrity and utter professionalism he was regularly the top seller in the group. \n\nI have no hesitation in recommending Alwin as a BDD for Intl Business events and Exhibitions. I wish him all the best for his continued career.", "recommendations/11/name": "Alvin Wee, CEM, CIS", "recommendations/11/subtitle": "Group Director of Business Development and International MICE", "recommendations/11/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/alvin-wee-cem-cis-11a4739/", "recommendations/11/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGri-YBDaMlbWeTow9Sn0hmRxZ5ChKL7IQ", "recommendations/12/context": "David Richard managed Hassan directly", "recommendations/12/date": "May 10, 2024", "recommendations/12/description": "I had the pleasure of working with Hassan for the better part of 3 years @ Marriott.\n\nWithout doubt one of the most talented, customer focused and revenue driven hoteliers in the capital. Always willing and able to find a solution to all the challenges that the operation throws at you. \nHis enthusiasm for the job is second to none. On call to the guest, team and stakeholders 24/7.\n\nHe has a deep knowledge and understanding of revenue management, thus enabling him to bring this skill to new practitioners of the art. His approach to all who worked with him wants Hassan to reach the pinnacle of our profession - next stop as DoR on the horizon.\n\nI have no hesitation in recommending Hassan and willingly available to be contacted for direct feedback.", "recommendations/12/name": "Hassan Khan", "recommendations/12/subtitle": "Cluster Revenue Manager at Hashoo Group", "recommendations/12/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/hassan-khan-42a8ba132/", "recommendations/12/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAACCGgOIBRnanfXrlom3YxpVCWBYuK4gbY0s", "recommendations/13/context": "David Richard managed Amina directly", "recommendations/13/date": "May 9, 2024", "recommendations/13/description": "Amina was truly fantastic to work with. \n\nA continuous presence in the hotel who could see trends in the market place before anyone else. Her contribution to the operational and fiscal success of the hotel was clear to all who worked with her. \nHighly articulate, well groomed and an all round hotel professional. \n\nAmina is every GM's dream for the marketing department. She will continually be coming up with new ideas/promotions/campaigns to promote, market and sell the property. \n\nI have no hesitation in recommending Amina and would gladly work with her again", "recommendations/13/name": "Amina J.", "recommendations/13/subtitle": "Experienced Marketing Director with 12+ Years in Hospitality | Driving Brand Growth through Innovative Strategies”", "recommendations/13/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/amina-j-a43724b0/", "recommendations/13/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABeZltMBH4ljLcrzBbbZoLWCGENjKR4N7cs", "recommendations/14/context": "David Richard managed Nadeem directly", "recommendations/14/date": "May 9, 2024", "recommendations/14/description": "I had the pleasure of working with Nadeem @ Avari Towers in KarachiI. \nWhen I joined in February 2014 he was a restaurant manager. Due to his work ethic, diligence, integrity and strong professional approach, he was made acting assistant FBM. \nI have no hesitation in recommending Nadeem and wish him all the best for his continued career.", "recommendations/14/name": "Nadeem Khan", "recommendations/14/subtitle": "Restaurant Manager", "recommendations/14/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/nadeem-khan-75215015/", "recommendations/14/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAML9S4Bjrvd5uAz5tZBXiLh-klIDeVkKvQ", "recommendations/15/context": "David Richard managed Ayesha directly", "recommendations/15/date": "May 9, 2024", "recommendations/15/description": "I employed Ayesha @ Marriott. Initially bought in as the QAM kitchen production and related areas. \n\nShe very quickly showed an aptitude for taking on more areas of responsibility and projects. \nShe is an excellent team player however she can also work independently to ensure timelines are met and SOPs / P&Ps are adhered to strictly. Her follow up is continuous and will not let an opportunity pass to improve herself and the property pass.\n\nAyesha took on the QAM role for the whole property and started from scratch in implementing sustainability in line with Marriott International guidelines / standards. \nExceptionally detailed, very strong work ethic, will work all hours, never leaves something undone, team player, smart, excellent customer contact and highly professional. \n \nI have no hesitation in recommending Ayesha for any role related to her expertise and areas where she wants to improve herself.", "recommendations/15/name": "Ayesha Zainab", "recommendations/15/subtitle": "Cluster Hygiene manager Approved highfield tutor| Approved TSI tutor lBRCGS Food LAC| ISO14001 LA l FSSC LAC | ISO9001 LAC | HACCP 4 Highfield", "recommendations/15/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ayesha-zainab-55419a1b8/", "recommendations/15/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAADKSq5ABC6OChV4X0oZ_l5-i-IcZgkbcM3g", "recommendations/16/context": "David Richard managed Ahtesham directly", "recommendations/16/date": "May 9, 2024", "recommendations/16/d