 "recommendationsReceived/2/date": "April 5, 2025", "recommendationsReceived/2/description": "Almost one year I worked with Mr. David. \nVery wise and detailed, the hotel revenue improvement is much better than the hotel revenue in the previous 2 years.\nMr. David is one of the best General Managers in charge of 1357 staff and daily workers, with a significant increase in revenue compared to the previous year. Excellent communication with all HODs and all staff, detailed, hardworking, whenever needed always willing to come directly to the location, understand the conditions of subordinates, prioritize guests and good service for all guests and employees.\nDuring his leadership many improvement projects were carried out such as:\nRenovation of 68 new guest rooms from a total of 772 existing rooms with a total budget of 7 billion. \n\nLVMD main panel replacement with a total repair of 3.2 billion \n\nand there are still many improvement projects approved by Mr. David to improve the quality of hotel guest services with a total value of 27 billion during 2024.", "recommendationsReceived/2/name": "Syahban Hasibuan", "recommendationsReceived/2/subtitle": "Director Of Engineering Hotel Borobudur Jakarta", "recommendationsReceived/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/syahban-hasibuan-4a078438/", "recommendationsReceived/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAfx-bgBZucGaoIoiomPx8kDjdC96QZ_qns", "recommendationsReceived/3/context": "Gunung reported directly to David Richard", "recommendationsReceived/3/date": "March 6, 2025", "recommendationsReceived/3/description": "I have had the privilege of working alongside Mr. David Richard as our General Manager at Hotel Borobudur Jakarta. It is truly an honor to work under the leadership of someone as inspiring and visionary as you. \n\nAnd it has been an incredible journey working alongside such an inspiring leader and a dynamic team at Hotel Borobudur Jakarta. Your guidance and vision have played a significant role in shaping my approach to revenue management and strategic decision-making.\n\nI firmly believe that success in this field is not just about numbers but about collaboration, innovation, and creating sustainable growth. I am grateful for the trust and opportunities given, and I look forward to continuously contributing to the hotel’s success and pushing the boundaries of what we can achieve together. Thank you once again for your support and leadership!", "recommendationsReceived/3/name": "Gunung Deca Riviera", "recommendationsReceived/3/subtitle": "Revenue and Ecommerce Manager at Borobudur Hotel, Jakarta", "recommendationsReceived/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/gunung-deca-riviera-138713b3/", "recommendationsReceived/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABgh6fwB7n1kAxfU-V10fo4WQS3mtgJ7vgY", "recommendationsReceived/4/context": "Ignatius reported directly to David Richard", "recommendationsReceived/4/date": "February 5, 2025", "recommendationsReceived/4/description": "I have the privilege of working closely with Mr. David Richard during his tenure as General Manager at Hotel Borobudur Jakarta. I take a moment to express my sincere appreciation for David’s leadership and guidance. His vision, support, open-door policy, positive energy has had a significant impact on the team.\nI particularly appreciate his constant insightful feedback on our performance; Focus on the task on hand and constantly motivated the team to go further.\n\nDavid’s dedication to the company's success, employee growth, creating a positive work environment is truly inspiring. I feel fortunate to be a part of your team and to learn from him.", "recommendationsReceived/4/name": "Ignatius Anugraham", "recommendationsReceived/4/subtitle": "Hotelier / Hospitality Industry", "recommendationsReceived/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ignatius-anugraham-3ab83131/", "recommendationsReceived/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAa1K_MB-glv_y9uOJOn9woDnw6vvXAVMb8", "recommendationsReceived/5/context": "Syed Mughees reported directly to David Richard", "recommendationsReceived/5/date": "September 15, 2024", "recommendationsReceived/5/description": "I had the privilege of working closely with Mr. David Richard during his tenure as General Manager of Islamabad Marriott Hotel. His leadership and strategic insight were instrumental in consistently meeting and exceeding all revenue targets. \n\nUnder his guidance, the hotel not only achieved its highest-ever revenue figures but also saw remarkable growth in guest satisfaction and operational efficiency. His ability to inspire and lead a diverse team while maintaining a focus on profitability is truly commendable.\n\n Mr. David is a results-driven leader who elevates both the business and the people around him. I highly recommend him for any leadership role in the hospitality industry.", "recommendationsReceived/5/name": "Syed Mughees Shah (SHRM-CP)", "recommendationsReceived/5/subtitle": "Director Human Resources | Strategic HR Leader | SHRM-CP | Driving Talent Transformation & Inclusion in Hospitality | Expert in Employee Engagement | Culture & Operational Excellence", "recommendationsReceived/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/mugheesshah/", "recommendationsReceived/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAImSRIBQ_mZ5yRfdH0sk9jRvC9j7VkeMuw", "recommendationsReceived/6/context": "Nisha reported directly to David Richard", "recommendationsReceived/6/date": "June 12, 2024", "recommendationsReceived/6/description": "I've had the privilege of working with Mr. David at the Marriott. His consistent encouragement, positive attitude, friendly advice and professional guidance have given me the confidence to grow. \n\nHe excels at inspiring and mentoring his team to achieve their best while also allowing them to work independently. I wish him all the best in his future endeavor!", "recommendationsReceived/6/name": "Nisha K.", "recommendationsReceived/6/subtitle": "Marketing Manager | Performance Marketing & Digital Growth | Hospitality", "recommendationsReceived/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/nisha-akhan/", "recommendationsReceived/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABk_Zb0BUZ6AB9q91mkIEsgEaYHutgM6Q84", "recommendationsReceived/7/context": "Aamir reported directly to David Richard", "recommendationsReceived/7/date": "June 8, 2024", "recommendationsReceived/7/description": "I have had the distinct pleasure of working alongside David O'H during the pivotal moments in my career at Avari Group, and I can unequivocally state that David is an extraordinary General Manager whose impact on the hospitality industry is profound and far-reaching.\n\nDavid's over 25 years of extensive experience across SE Asia, South Asia, the Middle East, and Europe is a testament to his unparalleled expertise and adaptability. His proficiency in managing boutique, deluxe, and mid and large-scale establishments, coupled with his deep understanding of both operational and financial intricacies, positions him as a leader of exceptional caliber.\n\nUnder David’s stewardship, I witnessed firsthand his remarkable ability to turn around hotel operations, driving positive business outcomes while significantly enhancing both tangible and intangible service elements. His passion for developing internal talent is truly inspiring; he is dedicated to nurturing and broadening the skill sets of his team, ensuring a culture of continuous improvement and excellence.\n\nDavid’s strategic approach to hotel management is characterized by his profound understanding of local cultures and psychologies, which he adeptly integrates into innovative strategies that resonate with diverse markets. His European training, combined with extensive exposure to various regions and ethnic backgrounds, makes him an adept cultural navigator in the hospitality landscape.\n\nSpecializing in food and beverage, David excels in revenue management and employs situational leadership that is both hands-on and proactive. His strategic planning capabilities, coupled with his expertise in project management, particularly in pre and post-opening scenarios, are invaluable assets to any hotel operation.\n\nDavid’s proactive and transparent communication with on-site owners fosters trust and collaboration, ensuring alignment with overall business goals and strategies.\n\nIn summary, any hotel owner would choose David O’H with their eyes closed to elevate their establishment to unparalleled heights of success. His leadership, professionalism, and dedication to building champion teams make him an indispensable asset in the hospitality industry.\n\nI have no hesitation in endorsing David O'H, as a transformative leader whose vision and execution drive exceptional results. His commitment to excellence and team development is unmatched, making him the quintessential choice for any hotel aiming for top-tier performance and growth.", "recommendationsReceived/7/name": "Aamir Khawaja", "recommendationsReceived/7/subtitle": "General Manager | Four Points by Sheraton Lahore (Marriott International) | Hospitality Leader Transforming Hotel Performance, Revenue Strategy & Guest Experience | Former Senior GM @ Centaurus Towers Residencia & Suites", "recommendationsReceived/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/aamirkhj/", "recommendationsReceived/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAN0fpwBmZWjm4ko-Cyqzqz-rdj6gSZmuDQ", "recommendationsReceived/8/context": "Asim reported directly to David Richard", "recommendationsReceived/8/date": "May 19, 2024", "recommendationsReceived/8/description": "I had the pleasure of working with David twice – Avari Hotel Lahore and Marriott International, Pakistan \n \nWithout doubt one of the most professional and honest hoteliers in the industry. His enthusiasm for the job is second to none. His direct and understanding approach to guests and staff alike is exemplary \n\nDavid is a leader who you’ll always find in the middle of the action. He leads by example and is one of the most hands-on General Managers I have worked with. He always places his team first and is not afraid to back them when and where required\n\nI personally can vouch that as part of his team, I was always comfortable to make decisions and contribute to the goals of achieving revenue and guest satisfaction at the highest level\n\nHe has always given me great advice regarding my career and to this day is a mentor who guides me through the ups and downs of my professional career\n\nIt would be an honor to be a part of his team again if given a chance as professional leaders like him are rare to find in today’s workplace \n\nIn a nutshell - a 'professional hotelier who loves his job'", "recommendationsReceived/8/name": "Asim Khalid", "recommendationsReceived/8/subtitle": "Corporate Head Food & Beverage/Acting Hotel Manager", "recommendationsReceived/8/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/asim-khalid-b3a6036/", "recommendationsReceived/8/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAEoQp4BXuERdJb2zQIWRVryovtjjTadSBg", "recommendationsReceived/9/context": "Hassan reported directly to David Richard", "recommendationsReceived/9/date": "May 13, 2024", "recommendationsReceived/9/description": "I had the privilege of working alongside Mr. David Richard as our General Manager, and it was truly a remarkable experience. What sets Mr. David apart is his exceptional operational and financial acumen coupled with his unparalleled hospitality skills, making him a valuable asset for any hotel. He possesses the rare ability to seamlessly blend strategic thinking with hands-on management, ensuring that hotel operations run smoothly while also driving financial success.\n \nAs a leader, Mr. David is not only a coach and mentor but also a source of inspiration. His extraordinary wit and intelligence create an environment where learning is not only encouraged but also enjoyable. He has a keen sense of the pulse of the hotel industry, always staying ahead of trends and developments.\n \nOne of Mr. David's greatest strengths is his approachability. From line-level staff to executive committee members, he fosters an environment where everyone feels valued and heard. His management style is empowering, providing ample support for associates to grow and excel in their roles as hospitality professionals.\n \nMoreover, Mr. David's multicultural and diverse experience brings a unique perspective to his leadership. He understands the nuances of working in different cultural contexts and leverages this knowledge to create inclusive and welcoming environments for both guests and staff.\n \nIn conclusion, I wholeheartedly recommend Mr. David Richard as a General Manager. His combination of expertise, leadership qualities, and dedication to excellence make him an invaluable asset to any hospitality organization.", "recommendationsReceived/9/name": "Hassan Khan", "recommendationsReceived/9/subtitle": "Cluster Revenue Manager at Hashoo Group", "recommendationsReceived/9/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/hassan-khan-42a8ba132/", "recommendationsReceived/9/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAACCGgOIBRnanfXrlom3YxpVCWBYuK4gbY0s", "recommendationsReceived/10/context": "David Richard was senior to Alvin but didn't manage Alvin directly", "recommendationsReceived/10/date": "May 11, 2024", "recommendationsReceived/10/description": "I am writing to provide a heartfelt recommendation for Mr. David O Hanlon, with whom I had the pleasure of working closely during my Royal Cliff career from 2005 – 2008.\n\nMr. David O Hanlon is an exceptional leader with a keen ability to navigate complex challenges while fostering a positive and inclusive work environment. His dedication to excellence and passion for driving results were evident in every aspect of their work.\n\nOne of Mr. David’s most admirable qualities is his strong strategic vision. He possesses a remarkable talent for analyzing market trends, identifying opportunities, and developing innovative solutions to propel the organization forward. His insights were invaluable in shaping the company's growth strategy, leading to significant achievements and milestones.\n\nMoreover, Mr. David is a natural collaborator who excels at building and nurturing relationships across teams and stakeholders. Their effective communication skills and empathetic leadership style create a culture of trust and collaboration, inspiring everyone around them to strive for excellence.\n\nIt would be a great pleasure to be able to work alongside with him again anytime in the future.", "recommendationsReceived/10/name": "Alvin Wee, CEM, CIS", "recommendationsReceived/10/subtitle": "Group Director of Business Development and International MICE", "recommendationsReceived/10/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/alvin-wee-cem-cis-11a4739/", "recommendationsReceived/10/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGri-YBDaMlbWeTow9Sn0hmRxZ5ChKL7IQ", "recommendationsReceived/11/context": "Amina reported directly to David Richard", "recommendationsReceived/11/date": "May 9, 2024", "recommendationsReceived/11/description": "It was an honor to work under the leadership of Mr. David. His management style was fair and supportive, which fostered a positive work environment for us. Under his guidance, we achieved significant success in our marketing initiatives. Mr. David's strategic insight and personal involvement in guiding our team were crucial in enhancing our brand's visibility and guest satisfaction. I wholeheartedly recommend him as a leader who truly inspires his team to bring out the best in them.", "recommendationsReceived/11/name": "Amina J.", "recommendationsReceived/11/subtitle": "Experienced Marketing Director with 12+ Years in Hospitality | Driving Brand Growth through Innovative Strategies”", "recommendationsReceived/11/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/amina-j-a43724b0/", "recommendationsReceived/11/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABeZltMBH4ljLcrzBbbZoLWCGENjKR4N7cs", "recommendationsReceived/12/context": "David Richard was senior to Nadeem but didn't manage Nadeem directly", "recommendationsReceived/12/date": "May 